'''Texas Tech University''' ('''TTU''') is a [[public university|public]], coeducational, research university in [[Lubbock, Texas|Lubbock]], [[Texas]], [[United States]]. Established on February 10, 1923, and originally known as Texas Technological College, it is the leading institution of the [[Texas Tech University System]] and has the [[List of largest Texas universities by enrollment|seventh largest]] student body in the state of Texas. With {{convert|1839|acre|km2}}, it has the second largest contiguous campus in the United States and is the only school in Texas to house an undergraduate institution, [[law school]], and [[medical school]] at the same location.
